Be able to use names that are in fields in a comment the same way as you can use the @mention feature.  For example, I could type @[Assignee] and it would replace it with the name of the assignee at the time I type it and make it work just like an @mention does, sending a "mentioned you" email to the assignee.

This would be EXTREMELY beneficial when incorporated with the Mass update tool.  I run a query of all sub-tasks without an estimate and could then send a message like "@[Assignee], please enter an estimate for your sub-task".  It would replace the @[Assignee] with the assignee's name at the time of the comment entry (bulk update) for each issue and send a "mentioned you" email to the assignee.

