If you enter in something like .2125h in a timetracking field in Jira, it will save successfully - but when any edit is made to the issue after that, there is an error next to those fields saying that the value is incorrect, because it is converted to 12.75m.  

Since entering in a long decimal into one of these fields results in an error, it would probably be best to display an error right away, not allowing the user to do this in the first place.

