The "Current Status" custom field on JAC is the best invention since sliced bread (OK maybe since JIRA itself). It make it _much_ easier for an administrator to be informed of the progress of an issue and plan accordingly (especially when the status says there is no short term plan to implement the fix or suggestion).

 

The challenge is to be able to catch this via a JQL filter.

{{"Current Status" CHANGED}}

is not possible.

I couldn't find any other event that could be used to trigger a filter.

