We develop the add-on TeamCity Integration for JIRA, which requires creation of the applink to TeamCity server. While entering the address, JIRA requests accessibility of the manifest (the way it does for native products), but TeamCity does not return anything, so it shows that the specified address is inaccessible.
Is it possible to add a capability allowing applinks to define whether it should request or not manifest and the place where it is requested from?
This will also improve the procedure of applink creation, when entry of the URL will automatically create the applink (the same way it works for Confluence and so on).

