According to [this documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jira/advanced-use-of-the-jira-issue-collector-296092376.html#AdvancedUseoftheJIRAIssueCollector-EmbeddingtheIssueCollector], in order to *embed* the Issue Collector with your Confluence instance, you would need to use the *[HTML Include|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/html-include-macro-169120653.html]* macro:

{quote}
The Issue Collector can be embedded into Confluence using the HTML Include Macro. Note that using the HTML Include Macro would require you to embed the Issue Collector code separately on each page.
{quote}

However, in order to embed the Issue Collector code in Confluence, instead of using the Include macro, the user will nee to use the [HTML Macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/html-macro-38273085.html], which will generate the HTML content in the pages. The only correction needed would be to remove the 'Include' word and change to HTML macro using the link above. :)
